### Hadith 3:423

*Narrated 'Urwa bin Az-Zubair:*

Hakim bin Hizam said, "O Allah's Apostle! I used to do good deeds in the
Pre-lslamic period of Ignorance, e.g., keeping good relations with my
Kith and kin, manumitting slaves and giving alms. Shall I receive a
reward for all that?" Allah's Apostle replied, "You embraced Islam with
all the good deeds which you did in the past."

